{
  "texts": [
    "What matters-and is in our view left largely unaddressed by existing standards-is a more careful set of standards relating the 'weighting' and 'voteprediction' procedure.",
    "6 We can categorise models used by AI pollsters to generate weights and predict vote-choice for a population of interest under two broad families: parametric models (Park et al. 2004; Hanretty et al. 2018; Hanretty 2019; Lauderdale et al. 2020), and non-parametric models (Bisbee 2019; Ornstein 2019; Broniecki et al. 2022).",
    "(1) Parametric models: these are models characterised by a defined, restricted set of of interpretable and theoretically motivated set of parameters and variables.",
    "The input to these models is a sample of respondents, which is processed by a ML algorithm to generalise its features to the broader population.",
    "These generalised predictions for each 'cell' in the population are then assigned weights-which may themselves be generated as the result of modeling."
  ]
}